SIMPLE: propend
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Propend
<hw>Pro*pend"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>propendere</ets>, <ets>propensum</ets>; <ets>pro</ets> forward,
forth + <ets>pendere</ets> to hang. See <er>Pendent</er>.]</ety> <def>To
lean toward a thing; to be favorably inclined or disposed; to incline;
to tend.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We shall <qex>propend</qex> to it, as a stone falleth down.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propendency</ent>⟦br⟧
